HEADWORD: Seljuckian
<hw>Sel*juck"i*an</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>A member of the family of
<persfn><etsep>Seljuk</etsep></persfn>; an adherent of that family, or
subject of its government;</def> (<pluf>pl.</pluf>) <def>the dynasty of
Turkish sultans sprung from Seljuk.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

